Male, 40 - 59 years

Age Reported Symptoms Notes
40 2021-01-03 lacrimation increased This is a 40 y.o. female who presents with abrupt onset of nausea vomiting, diarrhea, myalgias, head... Read more
Close
This is a 40 y.o. female who presents with abrupt onset of nausea vomiting, diarrhea, myalgias, headache about 2 hours after receiving her 1st Moderna COVID-19 vaccine at 1300 hrs.. She describes myalgias extending from the area of her left deltoid injection site over her shoulders and over her entire upper body. No neck or back pain. She describes diffuse throbbing headache with no positional component. She has had relentless nausea vomiting and retching. She has been up vomiting stomach contents to bile multiple times. She has had loose watery brown diarrhea multiple times. She describes diffuse abdominal crampy pain with increased tearing retching and vomiting. She denies any shortness of breath cough or wheezing. Voice is normal. No swallowing dysfunction or pain. No intraoral or facial swelling. She denies rash or pruritus. No arthralgias. Patient reports prior anaphylaxis with shortness of breath and tight airways, difficulty speaking and swallowing, and relationship to coconut ingestion few years prior. No other known food/nut reactions. Patient is a CNA for care at home. Last Covid test was 2 weeks ago which was negative. She reports she has been tested every 2 weeks routinely. Review of Systems Cardiovascular: Negative for chest pain and palpitations. Gastrointestinal: Positive for abdominal pain, diarrhea and nausea. Negative for vomiting. Musculoskeletal: Positive for myalgias. Negative for arthralgias, back pain and neck pain. Neurological: Positive for headaches. Negative for dizziness, weakness and numbness. Physical Exam BP 126/73 | Pulse 120 | Temp 37.1 °C (98.8 °F) | Resp 18 | Ht 1.575 m (5' 2") | Wt 68 kg (150 lb) | SpO2 100% | BMI 27.44 kg/m² ED Course as of Dec 30 2340 Wed Dec 30, 2020 2128 Reevaluation: Nausea improved. Abdominal cramping resolved. No further diarrhea or vomiting. Still complains of headache and muscle cramping through her upper shoulders and arm. Will remedicate with steroid and acetaminophen 2258 Reevaluation: Patient improved. Pain/myalgias improved. Headache now mild and dull. Continues with no further.nausea vomiting or diarrhea. She would like to try fluids at this time. Assuming toleration we will plan on discharge home. 2326 Reevaluation: Patient feels improved. Headache essentially gone. Taking p.o. fluids well. Discharge instructions discussed. She is very familiar with an EpiPen because of her daughter's prior use. Discharge instructions discussed. ASSESSMENT and PLAN This is a 40 y.o. female who presents with nausea vomiting diarrhea, myalgias, diffuse abdominal cramping, severe global headache, onset about 2 hours after first dose Moderna COVID-19 vaccine. Exam with intact mental status, neurologic system. Abdomen with some diffuse tenderness but no evidence of peritoneal sign. She had diffuse palpable soft tissue muscular type tenderness through her upper extremity shoulder and bilateral paraspinal back. She had no meningeal signs. She had no cardiorespiratory signs or symptoms. Her chest was clear. Voice normal. Swallowing normal. Oropharyngeal region normal. Initial ED ED management focused on rehydration, antiemetics and subsequent treatment for presumptive anaphylaxis with likely system involvement gastrointestinal and neurologic. She was treated with Solu-Medrol, famotidine and acetaminophen. She improved during ED course and did not require epinephrine. Symptoms at ED reevaluation/discharge were resolved. Clinical impression favors anaphylaxis over medication side effect given time course and abrupt onset of symptomatology and signs. She has a distant history of anaphylaxis to coconut-based product in her past. She has no history of ongoing allergic chronic history otherwise. Other organ systems appeared stable at onset and through ED course including cardiovascular and pulmonary. Plan is for discharge home with rest fluids. She will have a course of steroids/prednisone and famotidine. She was sent home with an EpiPen and understands use and precautions. Discussed ED "return immediately if" parameters with patient. Ongoing FOLLOW UP evaluation/care coordination via PCP recommended. Patient voices good understanding of current evaluation, follow-up & return recommendations and discharge instructions. Encounter Diagnosis Anaphylaxis due to vaccination, initial encounter Plan: -d/c home. No work next 2 days. Off work note provided -COVID-19 testing pending -rest with activity as tolerated -diet as tolerated & increased fluids as discussed -acetaminophen PRN -Prednisone 40 mg daily to finish 4 more days -Famotidine 40 mg daily to finish 4 more days -Zofran as needed (patient has at home) -Loratadine 10 mg OTC as needed -PCP f/u -ED return for interval worsening -instructions discussed & as documented
40 2021-01-04 taste impairment At about 1330 on 30DEC, the patient received the 1st dose of the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine. Less tha... Read more
Close
At about 1330 on 30DEC, the patient received the 1st dose of the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine. Less than five minutes after the vaccine was administered, the patient noticed a metallic taste. About two to three minutes afterwards, the patient noticed a ?tingling? sensation mostly on the left side of the face and minimally on the right side. Almost immediately after the ?tingling? sensation, the patient felt the sensation of an increased heart rate and checked his pulse with his watch that had a pulse sensor. The watch indicated that he had a heart rate of 115 bpm. This sensation of an increased heart rate subsided after for one or two minutes and repeat pulse measurement was in the low 90s. Towards the end of the 15 minute post-vaccination observation period, the medical technician did the final check on the patient. The patient admitted to experiencing a metallic taste and a mild tingling sensation on the neck and face area. The service member was immediately brought back to the treatment room were a faint red rash and was noticed on the left side of the neck by the medical providers present. Two doses of Benadryl 25mg were given and the patient was told to continue to be observed in the observation area. After about 20 minutes, the tingling sensation resolved. The patient checked his pulse again and it was in the low 70s. The metallic taste resolved after about one and a half hours after the start of the symptom.

My upper left cheek and the side of my left eye have a constant, moderate burning feeling. The shot was in my left arm. The Dr. at urgent care said it was not a stroke, so that's good. I have never experienced anything like this before. It has now been over 13 hours.
40 2021-01-23 swelling around the eyes The shot was administered in my left arm. I experienced localized swelling and axillary lymph node ... Read more
Close
The shot was administered in my left arm. I experienced localized swelling and axillary lymph node tenderness immediately after injection under my left armpit. The right side of my face also became numb for about 5 minutes. The next morning the areas around my eyes were swollen and I had two styes in my right eye. I do not know if these were related. These symptoms lasted approximately 3 days. Some minimal swelling and tenderness seemed to remain, and approximately a week later I experienced a painful resurgence of the swelling at the injection site that was far larger, harder and more painful. I took Benadryl and Ibuprofen. These relieved the symptoms within 48 hours.

About 1am, as I prepared for bed, it had become red and was quite irritated. I went to sleep and woke up in the middle of the night and my eye was quite irritated and it was filled with tears. 40 2021-03-03 ear pain Received first dose of Moderna vaccine on Tuesday 2/23/2021 and began to feel tingling on the right ... Read more
Close
Received first dose of Moderna vaccine on Tuesday 2/23/2021 and began to feel tingling on the right side of my head and an ear ache the next day (Wednesday 2/24/2021). The symptoms got progressively worse over the next few days and on Sunday 2/28/2021 the right side of my face was completely paralyzed. I sought emergency care at Hospital Emergency Room where I was diagnosed with Bells Palsy. The doctor who treated me strongly believes that the Bells Palsy was due to the Moderna vaccine. Today (9 days post vaccine) the entire right side of my face continues to be completely paralyzed with no signs of improvement.

40 2021-03-11 inability to speak Patient received vaccine at 3:15 pm on 3/12/21 and stayed in pharmacy area for 15 min (he left feeli... Read more
Close
Patient received vaccine at 3:15 pm on 3/12/21 and stayed in pharmacy area for 15 min (he left feeling fine). After about an hour 4:15 he showed back up at the pharmacy telling our pharmacy technician that he lost his voice and his throat was closing. She rushed him to the waiting room where I, pharmacist, came out and asked him what was going on. He stated he was with a client and suddenly lost his voice, and felt his throat starting to close. I asked if he was having trouble breathing and he said yes because his throat was closing and his whole arm was tingling. I had him take his mask down and try to take a few deep breaths first. I asked for permission to administer an Epi-pen which he gave verbal consent. 911 was called. Patient stated he did not want 911 called because he was going to refuse service. After a min or so patient stated his throat was back open and he was feeling good. I informed him paramedics are on their way and he needed to stay in the waiting room because effects of the EpiPen can wear off in 15 min. I stayed with him and watched until paramedics arrived. Paramedics sat with him and he did refuse service (they did take his blood pressure). When paramedics asked the patient about when he came in they asked if he was having trouble breathing and he responded "no I could breathe, my voice was just hoarse" (which is the opposite of what he told the technician and myself). He also sounded like it was very hard to breathe. I did information to the paramedics after saying that he told us his throat was closing of which they stated that they figured that was the case and they knew the patient and assumed he would refuse service. Patient was in contact with his primary care doctor who told him he could go home if his BP was ok but to make sure he had someone to drive him home. Patient had his wife come to get him and they left.

Condition aggravated; Palpitations; Tinnitus; This case was received on 01-Jun-2021 and was forwarded to Moderna on 01-Jun-2021. This regulatory authority case was reported by an other health care professional and describes the occurrence of CONDITION AGGRAVATED (Condition aggravated), PALPITATIONS (Palpitations) and TINNITUS (Tinnitus) in a 46-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 039A21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. Concurrent medical conditions included Blood pressure high, Asthma and Allergy NOS. Concomitant products included FLUTICASONE PROPIONATE, SALMETEROL XINAFOATE (ADVAIR) and LOSARTAN for an unknown indication. On 25-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 25-Mar-2021, the patient experienced CONDITION AGGRAVATED (Condition aggravated) (seriousness criterion disability), PALPITATIONS (Palpitations) (seriousness criterion disability) and TINNITUS (Tinnitus) (seriousness criterion disability). At the time of the report, CONDITION AGGRAVATED (Condition aggravated), PALPITATIONS (Palpitations) and TINNITUS (Tinnitus) had not resolved. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments. Immediately upon receiving injection, the patient's heart began racing, and what had been a relatively quite ringing in his ears for the past year or two, also immediately became 2-3x louder (maybe even more), where it had remained ever since (nearly 2 months). The heart rate settled down within a few second, but the ringing persisted, and continued. Before the vaccine, the ringing was a very high pitched, constant tone, like the high pitched tone he used to hear on an airplane sometimes, but it was so quiet that he only noticed when he would wake up in the morning or at other random times when everything around him was very quiet. Since the vaccine, however, it became loud enough that it was impossible not to notice it constantly; not so loud that he could not hear other things around him or people talking, but definitely loud enough that it was unmistakably there and could at times be a real distraction to focus and even conversation. Treatment medications were not reported. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments. Once, for a short time while performing a mild workout in the gym, and again a couple hours later, and for an extended duration (approximately 40 minutes), while checking out at Costco I experienced what I believe to have been aura migraines without headache (or ocular migraines) in my right eye. What initially appeared to be a slight glare, I later determined was an obscuration of the lower half of my vision in that eye which could be described as a clouding effect. While disorienting and concerning, with closing/covering that eye, the problem slowly resolved itself. Within about 20 minutes, I had enough vision to comfortably and safely drive home. Another 20 minutes after that and the event had ended as far as I could tell. I have never experienced anything like this in the past. Doing some (dangerous, I know) searching online, I discovered what it might be called and learned that there were some reports of similar events occurring with other vaccine recipients. Since I don't have a primary care physician, I'm hoping it is directly related to the vaccine and I hope it doesn't happen again with the second dose since my eyes are a critical part of my job.

The morning after I received the vaccine, I woke up and I had flu like symptoms. I had a low grade fever, some nausea, ringing in my ears and fatigue. By bedtime that night, I felt normal except for the tinnitus that stayed. I went to the doctor on 03/26, an audiologist, and she told me that it is tinnitus and she had another patient that got tinnitus after the vaccine also. I am having a lot of trouble hearing now. The doctor told me that the ringing that I hear is a short circuit in my brain. It's not so much in my ear, but from the processing of the brain. I will follow up with the doctor in a year.

The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant medications were not reported. On 09 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 025J20A), intramuscularly in left arm, for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 10 Jan 2021, he was sore, felt like had the flu. On 13 Jan 2021, he experienced light sensitivity, and tearing of his right eye. On 19 Jan 2021, he went to the emergency room and found with facial paralysis, droopiness on the right side. He was diagnosed with Bell's palsy (right eye won't blink on its own, lip and speech issues). Treatment included Valtrex. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided. The outcome of the event, sore, felt like had the flu was considered resolved on 11 Jan 2021. The outcome of the event, Bell's palsy (right eye won't blink on its own, lip and speech issues) was not recovered. The outcome of the events, light sensitivity, and tearing of right eye was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 50-year-old male patient. The medical history is not provided. The events of Influenza and Pain occurred approximately one day after receiving their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 025J20A). Photophobia and Lacrimation increased occurred approximately four days after the first dose of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 025J20A). Event of Facial Paralysis was diagnosed approximately ten days after the first dose of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 025J20A). Treatment included Valtrex. Close
Experienced Sudden Sensorineural Hearing Loss (SSNHL) in the left ear beginning in early morning on March 24, 2021. Hearing loss occurred over the course of approximately 1 hour. Initial care sought through an urgent care on March 24, followed by my primary care physician on March 26, and then emergency room on March 27. Emergency room consulted with Dr and began treatment with oral course of prednisone, 50mg tablet once per day for a total of 6 days. Referred to Dr, ENT, on an emergent basis. Full audiological testing performed on March 29 at Dr office showed profound hearing loss (80-110 db) across all frequencies in left ear, with a speech recognition of 0%. Also experienced aural fullness and tinnitus in left ear. Received intratympanic injections of dexamethasone at Dr office on March 29, April 6 and April 15. I began to notice extremely gradual improvement of ability to hear starting on March 30, with slow incremental improvement continuing to date, but so far only partial recovery has occurred. A second full audiological assessment was performed on April 15 at Dr office, and results showed left ear hearing had improved to "asymmetric mild sloping to profound" hearing loss (25 -95 db from low to high frequencies), speech recognition improved to 48%. Complete recovery has been described as unlikely, but final recovery level is unknown and will be assessed in the coming months - most recovery from SSNHL occurs in the initial month following onset. Next appointment will be in 6 months to assess final hearing level in left ear and discuss amplification (hearing aid) if necessary.

51 2021-04-25 vision blurred, blindness in both eyes State opened Covid vaccines to 50 and over on Mon, March 22. I immediately scheduled my appointment ... Read more
Close
State opened Covid vaccines to 50 and over on Mon, March 22. I immediately scheduled my appointment for a first shot at a Dept of Health site near me for Wed, March 24. I had no immediate negative side effects. When I woke on Fri, March 26 and commenced my day of remote work from home, I noticed my left eye vision was blurry. I proceeded to work that day and continued my normal activities into the weekend assuming my vision would self-correct. By Sunday, March 26, my left eye vision was still noticeably problematic so I scheduled to see an optometrist whom I had seen before. I saw him at 12:15pm on Tues, March 30. After running numerous vision tests, optometrist let me know my vision loss in the left eye seemed to be the result of a stroke that had cut blood flow in the optic nerve and damaged my vision in the lower portions of the left eye. The center and upper portions of my left eye were generally unaffected at that time. He suggested I see my primary care physician to check for vitals, such as blood pressure and do other blood work, and more importantly see a neuro ophthalmologist urgently. The next morning, Wed, March 31 I saw my PCP, who informed me my blood pressure was normal, requested blood work, and gave me a prescription for an MRI of my brain, with and without contrast. I am 6'2" and I weighed at 239, about where it has been for most of last 15 years. I also complained of pain and stiffness in my front right thigh and lower right back. She said if I didn't get an appointment to see a neuro ophthalmologist that same afternoon, she recommended I go to an ER. With the help of Optometrist's office, I was able to get an appointment that day with Dr., neuro ophthalmologist at 2:15pm on Wed, March 31. His office repeated numerous vision tests and confirmed the left eye vision loss (essentially the lower half excluding the center) and diagnosed it as a NAION - non arthritic ischemic optic neuropathy. With this diagnosis, there was no treatment, and I scheduled a follow-up for May 12. He said that my optic nerve into my left eye would slowly reduce its swelling over the next 6 to 8 weeks and in that time, my vision could remain the same, or improve. At that point, I didn't think it would worsen, but sadly that later happened. In addition to the the first MRI that PCP prescribed, Neuro ophthalmologist prescribed a second MRI of orbits, with and without contrast. He also suggested I begin taking a low dose Aspirin daily, which I did. The next week, the blood work revealed a very slightly elevated cholesterol reading. I was told by my PCP on April 5 that this would normally not be considered as a problematic level of high cholesterol, but should be improved or lowered. The blood tests taken at Lab on Fri, April 2 revealed a LDL Chol, Calculated as 111, whereby <100 was considered desirable range. Other than that, there was nothing of concern in my blood work. The two MRIs were done on April 9 and April 20, and did not reveal findings which doctors felt would have impacted my optic nerve swelling or had caused the eye stroke. Out of precaution, I scheduled to see a cardiologist on Tues, April 13. She recommended I start taking Crestor for cholesterol, and do a series of tests which I completed on Friday, April 23 - echocardiogram; holter monitor; transesophageal echocardiogram; and ultrasound carotid bilateral. As of today, Mon, April 26 I do not know the results of the cardio work-up, but both neuro ophthalmologists I saw felt that a problem related to my heart would not have caused this stroke in my eye. Finally, on Fri, April 23 I had a consultation with a second highly recommended neuro ophthalmologist. After a series of vision tests, she agreed with other doctor's diagnosis of NAION - non arthritic ischemic optic neuropathy. She also said there was nothing I could do to treat except wait for the next 4 or more weeks for the optic nerve swelling to go down. She also confirmed my fear which was that my left eye vision had worsened since March 31 as my vision loss was no longer limited to the lower portion of my left eye, but now included blind spots throughout the upper range of my left eye vision, making my loss of peripheral vision worse and more widespread. She said in some cases with NAION, a patient's vision could remain the same, could improve or could worsen in the 6 to 8 weeks after the event. Four weeks after the March 26 event, by April 23 my left eye vision had worsened. I still hold out hope that it can improve some in the next four weeks... My right eye vision was not affected in any way, although one risk of NAION is that there is a 20% (?) chance it may recur in the next 5 years, and if it does, it most commonly affects the other, good eye. None of the doctors I saw directly attributed my vision loss to the Moderna vaccine taken on March 24; however, there has also not been a clear cause determined by my doctors. While most of the doctors I saw seemed to think it coincidental, none also was able to absolutely rule it out either as a cause or a trigger. Dr. suggested I follow through with this idea, which other medical professionals suggested, to submit this vaccine adverse event report. Without a doubt, this was an adverse effect and/or problem that occurred soon after (36 hours approximately) taking the first dose of the Moderna vaccine.

Everything came back negative and they found no cause for paralysis and assumed it was bells palsy. . I was put on prednisone and an anti-viral drug Baclamir (something that started with B ) . I was on about a weeks worth of the anti viral and about 10 days of the prednisone, and the first 8 days I was showing signs of improvement . I couldn't shut my left eye, raise my eyebrow, my whole face was numb on L side and I lost taste on L side of tongue. They did test me for Covid when I went to ER. I had a metallic taste in my mouth. It was the worst back acne possible, around 200 bumps on back that erupted overnight. The ER did r/o shingles but this rash was on several different nerve paths, it looked more like a reaction to the prednisone. I am an Archeologist and they ran a test to see if I had lyme disease because I come across ticks regularly but they came back negative for current and past infection. When I take Amoxicillin I do get heart palpitations and that's why I was on the doxycycline. I do take testosterone 1 shot a month in the hip. On the 8th day around 05/08/2021 it started to improve and every day after that was a 5% improvement.

This was very unfortunate 51 years old male with past medical history of hypertension, hyperlipidemia, obesity. Patient presented with chief complaint of shortness of breath and chest pain. EMS reported that the patient has been complaining of some shortness of breath and chest pain intermittent for couple of weeks. 12 leads EKG showed evidence of anterior ST elevation myocardial infarction. Code heart was called. Patient developed PEA arrest in the Cath Lab. CPR ACLS was initiated. ROSC was achieved initially after 30 minutes of CPR. Intra-aortic balloon pump was placed. Coronary arteries were essentially clean. Due to high suspicion for massive PE-TPA was given 100 mg without meaningful clinical improvement. CPR was continued for more than an hour. Despite all aggressive measures patient continued to deteriorate. At 3:26 PM patient has no spontaneous breathing, no peripheral pulses, no heartbeats by auscultation or by monitor. Pupils were fixed and dilated. No cough no gag reflexes . patient was pronounced dead.

Sensory hearing loss; hearing problem and could barely hear; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of HYPOACUSIS (hearing problem and could barely hear) and DEAFNESS NEUROSENSORY (Sensory hearing loss) in a 53-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch nos. 001B21A and 024M20A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The patient's past medical history included No adverse event. On 23-Feb-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 23-Mar-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 23-Mar-2021, the patient experienced HYPOACUSIS (hearing problem and could barely hear) (seriousness criterion medically significant). On 27-Mar-2021, the patient experienced DEAFNESS NEUROSENSORY (Sensory hearing loss) (seriousness criterion medically significant). At the time of the report, HYPOACUSIS (hearing problem and could barely hear) and DEAFNESS NEUROSENSORY (Sensory hearing loss) outcome was unknown. Treatment was provided with Prednisone and Valtrex Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded Reporter did not allow further contact; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded

Myasthenia gravis; Eye dropping just for a little bit; Double vision; Felt weak; Unable to stand up; This spontaneous case was reported by a patient (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of MYASTHENIA GRAVIS (Myasthenia gravis) in a 53-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. No medical history provided by the reporter. Concomitant products included PYRIDOSTIGMINE BROMIDE (MESTINON) and METFORMIN for an unknown indication. On 18-Feb-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 26-Mar-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On an unknown date, the patient experienced MYASTHENIA GRAVIS (Myasthenia gravis) (seriousness criterion medically significant), EYELID PTOSIS (Eye dropping just for a little bit), DIPLOPIA (Double vision), ASTHENIA (Felt weak) and DYSSTASIA (Unable to stand up). At the time of the report, MYASTHENIA GRAVIS (Myasthenia gravis), EYELID PTOSIS (Eye dropping just for a little bit), DIPLOPIA (Double vision), ASTHENIA (Felt weak) and DYSSTASIA (Unable to stand up) outcome was unknown. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): In 2021, Blood test: myasthenia gravis myasthenia gravis. After a week of vaccination, the patient experience double vision. Patient also said he got eye dropping just for a little bit and he felt weak. The patient went to hospital for eye exam and blood work. After the blood work, the team of doctor said he had myasthenia gravis, a autoimmune disease that affects the neuromuscular system and explained that his eye dropping was caused by muscle weakened. The physician advised him to have a surgery by removing his thymus gland and advised he might experience a myasthenia gravis crisis which could put his life in danger. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not applicable. No treatment information was provided. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

54 2021-03-09 pain in jaw Patient had usual post vaccination myalgias and lethargy for a few days after injection. These reso... Read more
Close
Patient had usual post vaccination myalgias and lethargy for a few days after injection. These resolved spontaneously. However, about a week after vaccination he developed recurrent fevers 102°F. He also had complaints of body aches and bilateral jaw pain. He had extensive evaluation including laboratory testing for infectious etiologies of his fever and none was identified. He was noted to have very high sed rate and CRP. When no specific etiology for his fevers could be identified we decided to proceed with a short course of prednisone which did seem to help his fever and jaw pain. After prednisone was stopped he had recurrence of fever and developed worse jaw pain and pain at the base of his neck. I examined him in clinic and found that he had a tender swollen thyroid. I directed him to the emergency department where CT scanning of his neck confirmed evidence of thyroiditis. TSH was undetectable and free T4 was about 2 times higher than normal. He was diagnosed with subacute thyroiditis. However, his symptomatology seemed quite dramatic for subacute thyroiditis, and the timing in relation to his vaccination is concerning for possible adverse vaccine reaction.

Had pain in my shoulder (and neck on my left side) as soon as the shot went in. I tried walking to the nearest convenience store to get some food and I felt I was experiencing vertigo. Several days after the vaccine I had a slight cough and sore throat. My glands in my neck under my jaw line are also swollen. Can my immune system really take another round of this? There are a couple other things that I have noticed. I don't seem to be thinking very clearly and I have noticed a remarkable number of type-os and poor syntax in emails that I send at work; this is not normal for me. Finally, after the shot, I noticed that my muscles, when doing a little exertion such as pushups, would build lactic acid quicker and more blood seemed to be delivered to my working muscles. I still have not regained my strength and tire more easierly when playing tennis or hitting against the tennis wall, for example. Note: May 24, 2021 the pharmacy that administered the COVID vaccines contacted me with some billing questions. When I mentioned my severe reactions, they told me they were filing a report upon my behalf. When done they told me it was the VAERS system and gave me a reference number (Ref-531994). I decided that not enough information would be in that report so wanted to submit myself because of my severe reaction and hospitalization. My PCP was not involved until after hospital for a follow up and I was seen by numerous doctors there, so I have no easy single POC until I dig more. Mar 26, 2021 Received first Moderna COVID vaccine lot 018B21A. Apr 13, 2021 Pain in knees begins and over approx. 18 hrs. increase rapidly to point of pain walking. Compression of knees to sit worse. Apr 14, 2021 Irritation in throat that felt like large amount of dry bread stuck. Cannot get rid of feeling. Lasts for approx. 36 hrs. Apr 16, 2021 Fingers begin randomly swelling one digit at a time with overlapping between fingers. Sections of my palms also (not entire palm at a time, just an area). Each swelling last between 18 to 36 hours. This swelling takes place from 21 Apr to 27 Apr. When a finger swells it becomes red, hot to the touch, and extremely itchy. I have pictures. Apr 17, 2021 Wake to find tongue hugely swelled. Thought I'd bitten in my sleep. Unable to eat, hard to swallow fluid past tongue. Lasts for a bit over 36 hrs. Apr 19, 2021 Knee pain begins spreading up thighs down calves. Pain also beginning in feet toes and ankles. Apr 20, 2021 Knee pain when bending prevents me from entering truck to drive. Apr 27, 2021 Knee pain eases slightly. Able to sit in truck for short period of time until too much pain. Apr 28, 2021 Receive second Moderna COVID vaccine lot 043B21A at 1pm. Apr 28, 2021 Approx. 2:30 pm knee/overall leg pain begins increasing rapidly to higher than before level. Over next three days increases to point where I cannot stand/walk due to pain. Unable to sleep due to pain also. Apr 28, 2021 Same Day-Around 4:30 pm notice voice is becoming raspy. By 6 pm my voice is completely gone. I have no voice for next approx. 36 hrs. Apr 30, 2021 Upper lip begins swelling in early afternoon. Enormous as everything else has been. Lasts approx. 36 hrs. but extremely tender for next 12 hrs. I have pictures. May 2, 2021 Go to ER in morning. Bloodwork/tests done. No conclusive results. Remain in ER overnight waiting for available bed at a hospital. May 3, 2021 Transferred by ambulance in afternoon to hospital. May 4, 2021 Begin seeing multitude of Drs. More bloodwork and testing. Still major pain w no relief. May 4, 2021 Suspected diagnosis is gout. I have never had gout diagnosed for me before but so be. May 4-7, 2021 Receive daily shot of anakinra. May 6, 2021 Begin noticing decrease in pain. Unable to get out of bed without help but attempting to use a walker. May 7, 2021 Lower lip begins swelling. Hospital staff injects BENADRYL. Even with, becomes, you guessed it, enormous. I have pictures. May 8, 2021 Discharged from hospital with walker. May 8-13, 2021 Required use of walker. Started using cane partially towards end date. May 14-present 2021 Using cane to walk. Less each day but still need for stability. Still have knee pain. Have higher level of pain in feet. I had/have a major reaction to the Moderna vaccine. This should be investigated and reported on. Thank you.

55 2021-05-13 loss of smell, hearing loss I acquired Covid on January 13. I was sick for three days, largely with headaches. I lost my sense o... Read more
Close
I acquired Covid on January 13. I was sick for three days, largely with headaches. I lost my sense of smell. After approximately 7 weeks, I had recovered most of my sense of smell. I received dose 1 of Moderna on March 2. Four days later I noticed that my sense of smell had diminished substantially. I contacted my primary and was assured that it wasn't a result of the vaccine. I saw an EENT, and he too assured me it wasn't because of the vaccine. I was put on Flonase and one course of steroids (12 days). After 2 weeks, my sense of smell was returning. I received my second dose on 3/30. Within 12 hours I knew something was wrong. My sense of smell seemed to be obliterated. It felt like there was a "hole" in the center of my nose. Within 36 hours, the turbinates in my nose were hypertrophic. I have never suffered seasonal allergies and had never even heard the word "turbinate" before this. 45 days later, my left nostril is blocked. My right nostril is nearly blocked. I have fluid behind both ears, and my hearing has diminshed. I feel completely let down by the medical establishment and even the CDC. There is no way that I should have been advised to have the vaccine just 40 days after contracting covid. All of the promises that the vaccine can't reduce sense of smell because there's no Covid in the vaccine are misleading. My immune system responded to the vaccine by attacking the site of the original infection, which was my nose. This has been devastating to me. I am depressed, anxious, and hopeless that this will correct itself. I will likely suffer some percentage of hearing loss. I was completely recovered from Covid, and it's only these vaccines that have ruined my health.

By Thursday, 3/11, it was apparent that the PVCs had stopped and heart rate was normal. I stopped the atenolol and the irregular heartbeat has not returned.

57 2021-05-17 taste impairment Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA For the first days following my 2nd shot my side effects where pretty s... Read more
Close
Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA For the first days following my 2nd shot my side effects where pretty standard. I tinfoil taste in my mouth after the shot, I had numbness in my left arm during the first night, I felt light headed on the 13th and had a fever over 100 F that evening. The 14th I was just sort of "floaty" and unfocused. I was fine while sitting, but if on my feet for more than a few minutes I got light headed and had to sit down. By Saturday the 15th I was pretty much back to normal and felt normal on Sunday the 16th. I went to work on Monday the 17th and worked a full shift from 5:00AM to 4:00PM without any noticeable side effects (maybe a bit higher fatigue than normal). On Tuesday the 18th everything went to (Bleep) I had a normal start arriving at work at 6:00AM and felt fine until about 7:30AM when I noticed that the panel I had just taken out of my machine looked bent. I grabbed a straight piece of wood to check it and it was straight. I then noticed that the line of holes also seemed to bend, that shouldn't happen. I raised my head and looked around a bit and noticed that everything looked a bit bent, sort of like looking through a fish-eye lens. It was a mild bending, but there. I took off my safety glasses thinking maybe they had gotten warped somehow, but it didn't change anything. Shortly after this I started feeling dizzy and unsteady on my feet. I reported this to my supervisor who told me to sit down and make sure to drink some fluids and rest during my 8:00AMbreak. I took a granola snack bar during break and drank half of my thermos of water. I sat for a good 10 minutes and started feeling better. I walked rather unsteadily back to my station and finished the job I was running at the tool, sitting down after starting each piece and then standing up to pull it off when it was done cycling. I got the job finished but still felt light headed and slightly dizzy. My supervisor told me to go home and I clocked out just before 9:00AM I went out to my car and rested for a few minutes then went over to the cafeteria to pick up my lunch and rested some more, then went back to the car. I waited awhile to see if I still felt dizzy and then left at about 9:30. The drive home is only 5 minutes, so I felt confident I would be OK as long as I took it slow and kept my vision fixed on the road directly in front of the car. I arrived at home and checked over my Covid-19 EUA and decided to call my vaccination/healthcare provider. They scheduled me to come in at 1:15PM and see the PA. I had a light lunch at 11:15AM and then took a nap until 12:30PM. My son drove me to my appointment, I was fine walking out to the car, and I didn't have any nausea or dizziness while in the car. When I was first led in the assistant took my weight, pulse, and BP. Surprise my blood pressure was 164/110! I've had slightly high blood pressure before, that is why I am on Lisinopril, but it is very mild, this surprised me! It apparently surprised the assistant as well since she took my BP again to be sure, and got the same result. I then stayed seated and waited for the doctor. She showed up a few minutes later and checked my blood pressure again. This time it was normal. Weird. She checked my eye tracking and heart rate and looked in my ears. General consensus is that it is high blood pressure and possibly inner ear. Most likely related to my covid-19 vaccine. She gave me a blood pressure monitoring sheet and told me to go home, rest, and drink lots of fluids. She sent a prescription for some nausea medication to my pharmacy (I haven't been to the pharmacy yet to pick it up). She will call me back to check up on me on Thursday after 4:00PM. In the meantime, I am to check my BP three times a day and anytime I am having an episode, and write it down on the form she gave me. I have a BP cuff at home, so no problems doing just that. I wrote about my symptoms on my Facebook page and got a reply from my daughter that said she had blurred vision issues after her second shot that lasted for almost the whole week. It may be something genetic. My son had his second shot on the 16th at 12:45PM. So far, other than a sore arm, he has shown no side effects at all. He had the Pfizer vaccine, while I had Moderna. It may have made a difference. I am just glad he is doing well.

59 2021-05-17 ear pain, eye pain, toothache I received the first Covid-19 vaccination 3/29/21. A few weeks later my grandkids (who previously h... Read more
Close
I received the first Covid-19 vaccination 3/29/21. A few weeks later my grandkids (who previously had a covid-19 positive illness months prior) came to visit from out of state for a few days. They were sick with colds. After they left, I got (presumably) the cold that they had and was sick for about a week. I postponed my 2nd dose of the Moderna Covid-19 vaccine until it had been 10 days of feeling better (although I did have mild headaches that ibuprofen seemed to quell). After receiving the the 2nd dose of the Moderna vaccine I began to have severe pain in one or two of my teeth, ear, and eye. I assumed it was dental related and spoke to my dentist who put me on amoxicillin and scheduled an appointment a week later. The pain and headaches intensified and I was taking a lot of ibuprofen and acetaminophen (max doses of each) to reduce the pain. At the time of my dental appointment my symptoms had lessened a bit and the dentist took x-rays that were inconclusive. She referred me to another dentist specialist who did the same thing and it was also inconclusive which tooth was bothering me or if there was even decay (under 2 crowns). The second dentist wanted me to come back after NOT taking any pain meds to make a definitive diagnosis. So, I stopped taking pain meds and the dental pain wasn't coming back. What DID come back though were the headaches which now I believed were migraine headaches that were treatable with Fioricet (a migraine med). Eventually, after maybe 14 days after the 2nd Moderna shot, the headaches finally disappeared...and my teeth are fine.

The extreme flu like symptoms lasted about 36 hours from onset the evening after the shot. over the course of 48 hours thereafter the symptoms gradually improved to the point where I felt just fine. I also experienced minor left arm pain from the injection. My arm was killing me for a week after the 1st injection!
